1
00:00:00,695 --> 00:00:02,834
(They kick off a romantic trip...)

2
00:00:02,835 --> 00:00:05,464
(with a beautiful sunrise.)

3
00:00:05,465 --> 00:00:06,634
(Full of laughter)

4
00:00:06,635 --> 00:00:08,105
(Full of happiness)

5
00:00:08,335 --> 00:00:09,435
The eldest!

6
00:00:09,605 --> 00:00:11,305
(The 5 brothers' happy family trip)

7
00:00:11,905 --> 00:00:13,674
(They take a special family portrait...)

8
00:00:13,675 --> 00:00:17,375
(and make some fun memories.)

9
00:00:17,715 --> 00:00:18,914
- San!
- Tan!

10
00:00:18,915 --> 00:00:20,214
They're both saying something else.

11
00:00:20,215 --> 00:00:25,455
(Today, they get to eat all they want.)

12
00:00:25,555 --> 00:00:28,355
(It's a happy vacation.)

13
00:00:28,485 --> 00:00:29,895
- Starting now...
- Yes?

14
00:00:30,655 --> 00:00:31,894
(Suddenly, they must fight for...)

15
00:00:31,895 --> 00:00:33,165
(a One-Bite Ticket.)

16
00:00:33,465 --> 00:00:34,465
Where is it?

17
00:00:34,466 --> 00:00:36,035
Yes. I am smart.

18
00:00:36,195 --> 00:00:37,795
I'll turn the tables at the last minute.

19
00:00:37,835 --> 00:00:39,905
(Who will win the One-Bite Ticket?)

20
00:00:42,735 --> 00:00:45,375
(DinDin gets it!)

21
00:00:46,805 --> 00:00:48,704
(2 Days 1 Night)

22
00:00:48,705 --> 00:00:50,575
(The eldest, second, third, fourth, youngest)

23
00:00:51,045 --> 00:00:52,075
No way.

24
00:00:52,185 --> 00:00:53,945
- This is the base camp?
- It's crazy.

25
00:00:54,445 --> 00:00:56,084
We're going all out.

26
00:00:56,085 --> 00:00:57,685
(They reach the base camp.)

27
00:00:58,415 --> 00:00:59,484
(They had a long day.)

28
00:00:59,485 --> 00:01:00,954
The rooms here are amazing.

29
00:01:00,955 --> 00:01:02,355
(They get a short break.)

30
00:01:03,425 --> 00:01:04,525
I'm hungry.

31
00:01:07,065 --> 00:01:08,625
- I'm hungry.
- I'm hungry too.

32
00:01:09,035 --> 00:01:10,595
Your voice goes so low.

33
00:01:10,665 --> 00:01:12,765
Shall we see whose voice can go lower?

34
00:01:13,705 --> 00:01:14,934
- Let's compete.
- Do it.

35
00:01:14,935 --> 00:01:16,904
I wonder. I've never lost so far,

36
00:01:16,905 --> 00:01:18,805
but I think you could beat me.

37
00:01:19,345 --> 00:01:21,645
- Do.
- Ti.

38
00:01:21,875 --> 00:01:24,045
- La.
- So.

39
00:01:24,215 --> 00:01:26,784
- Fa.
- Mi.

40
00:01:26,785 --> 00:01:28,515
Re.

41
00:01:28,915 --> 00:01:30,284
Do.

42
00:01:30,285 --> 00:01:31,815
- That's cool.
- So cool.

43
00:01:32,225 --> 00:01:34,925
Ti.

44
00:01:35,525 --> 00:01:37,194
His voice goes so low.

45
00:01:37,195 --> 00:01:38,224
(Fascinated)

46
00:01:38,225 --> 00:01:40,064
Will I end up burping while doing this?

47
00:01:40,065 --> 00:01:41,765
(Giggling)

48
00:01:42,765 --> 00:01:43,895
What's that note?

49
00:01:45,035 --> 00:01:47,164
(It's sounds like his voice went underground.)

50
00:01:47,165 --> 00:01:48,304
What's that?

51
00:01:48,305 --> 00:01:49,981
- It's like a turtle giving birth.
- What note is it?

52
00:01:50,005 --> 00:01:53,475
It really feels like we're a family of brothers on a trip.

53
00:01:53,545 --> 00:01:54,674
We're all fools.

54
00:01:54,675 --> 00:01:56,244
Five idiots traveling together.

55
00:01:56,245 --> 00:01:57,274
We're idiots?

56
00:01:57,275 --> 00:01:58,374
- Be nice.
- Who's there?

57
00:01:58,375 --> 00:01:59,414
What now?

58
00:01:59,415 --> 00:02:01,785
- There's a small bus outside.
- Okay.

59
00:02:02,115 --> 00:02:04,354
Joon is now licensed to drive large vehicles.

60
00:02:04,355 --> 00:02:05,454
- Yes.
- So...

61
00:02:05,455 --> 00:02:06,824
we want to let him practice.

62
00:02:06,825 --> 00:02:08,425
- Wait.
- I'll drive you home.

63
00:02:08,725 --> 00:02:10,324
How about you travel...

64
00:02:10,325 --> 00:02:12,324
- in a bus driven by Joon?
- What?

65
00:02:12,325 --> 00:02:13,325
That sounds scary.

66
00:02:13,326 --> 00:02:14,594
- It's too soon.
- No way.

67
00:02:14,595 --> 00:02:16,041
You haven't been on the road, have you?

68
00:02:16,065 --> 00:02:18,135
- He's still learning.
- I can practice.

69
00:02:18,465 --> 00:02:20,164
- Joon, have you driven...
- I'm anxious now.

70
00:02:20,165 --> 00:02:21,434
- since getting the license?
- No.

71
00:02:21,435 --> 00:02:23,075
- Sounds like fun.
- Do you want a go?

72
00:02:23,305 --> 00:02:24,634
I can manage no problem.

73
00:02:24,635 --> 00:02:26,545
It should be fun. Let's see what happens.

74
00:02:26,745 --> 00:02:28,604
When it comes to driving,

75
00:02:28,605 --> 00:02:30,215
- I can do basically anything.
- But...

76
00:02:30,445 --> 00:02:32,715
Later on, we could take the bus...

77
00:02:32,815 --> 00:02:35,445
- And run away.
- and escape back home.

78
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:38,014
We could drive into a five-star hotel...

79
00:02:38,015 --> 00:02:39,554
and announce we're taking over.

80
00:02:39,555 --> 00:02:41,024
Yes. Let's go on our own trip.

81
00:02:41,025 --> 00:02:42,354
Isn't this the bus?

82
00:02:42,355 --> 00:02:43,754
Is this the one?

83
00:02:43,755 --> 00:02:44,755
This is it.

84
00:02:44,756 --> 00:02:45,764
- You can drive this?
- Hey.

85
00:02:45,765 --> 00:02:47,664
- Can you even open the door?
- You bet I can.

86
00:02:47,665 --> 00:02:49,305
- Open it for us.
- I'll sit next to him.

87
00:02:49,465 --> 00:02:51,035
How do I turn on the indoor lights?

88
00:02:51,695 --> 00:02:53,404
- The first thing he said...
- I'm scared.

89
00:02:53,405 --> 00:02:54,725
Is how do you turn on the engine.

90
00:02:55,165 --> 00:02:56,634
How could you say that?

91
00:02:56,635 --> 00:02:57,774
I just do whatever.

92
00:02:57,775 --> 00:02:59,175
I'll shut the door.

93
00:02:59,275 --> 00:03:01,245
- Let's do one lap.
- Don't get excited, Joon.

94
00:03:01,345 --> 00:03:02,415
I'll close it now.

95
00:03:02,975 --> 00:03:03,975
(Feeling anxious)

96
00:03:03,976 --> 00:03:05,644
I'm uneasy seeing the way the door shut.

97
00:03:05,645 --> 00:03:06,645
Don't feel uneasy.

98
00:03:06,646 --> 00:03:08,884
Don't get carried away trying to show off.

99
00:03:08,885 --> 00:03:10,214
I can drive a 43-person bus.

100
00:03:10,215 --> 00:03:11,985
- This is a toy.
- It's a new challenge.

101
00:03:12,215 --> 00:03:14,184
- Why are you going so far?
- Where are you going?

102
00:03:14,185 --> 00:03:15,524
The food truck's there. Slow down.

103
00:03:15,525 --> 00:03:16,724
Slow down. It's beeping.

104
00:03:16,725 --> 00:03:18,405
- What's this noise?
- There's no beeping.

105
00:03:18,655 --> 00:03:20,094
What are you saying? There is a beeping.

106
00:03:20,095 --> 00:03:21,735
- Why is it beeping?
- What does it mean?

107
00:03:21,895 --> 00:03:23,034
The handbrake's on.

108
00:03:23,035 --> 00:03:24,565
The handbrake's on, you fool.

109
00:03:24,665 --> 00:03:26,665
- What are you doing?
- The handbrake!

110
00:03:26,965 --> 00:03:28,704
- That's really important.
- He's acting weird.

111
00:03:28,705 --> 00:03:29,734
- He's nervous.
- I'm not.

112
00:03:29,735 --> 00:03:30,735
- It's fine.
- What?

113
00:03:30,736 --> 00:03:32,104
- There are cars.
- Parked cars.

114
00:03:32,105 --> 00:03:33,574
- We can't get through.
- You turned too late.

115
00:03:33,575 --> 00:03:35,004
We can't get through.

116
00:03:35,005 --> 00:03:36,515
- We can't get through.
- We can.

117
00:03:36,975 --> 00:03:38,574
Are you checking both sides?

118
00:03:38,575 --> 00:03:40,244
- You're too close to the right.
- You made a big turn.

119
00:03:40,245 --> 00:03:41,985
- No.
- You're too far to the right.

120
00:03:42,755 --> 00:03:44,315
I'm doing fine.

121
00:03:45,015 --> 00:03:46,024
- Turn left?
- Yes.

122
00:03:46,025 --> 00:03:47,124
I can manage.

123
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:48,254
- Turn, then.
- Should I?

124
00:03:48,255 --> 00:03:49,294
You have my support if you make it.

125
00:03:49,295 --> 00:03:50,424
This is really tight.

126
00:03:50,425 --> 00:03:51,554
- My respect if you manage.
- Stay alert.

127
00:03:51,555 --> 00:03:53,194
Sir, could you make this turn?

128
00:03:53,195 --> 00:03:54,865
- Of course.
- This should be doable.

129
00:03:55,895 --> 00:03:56,964
It's doable.

130
00:03:56,965 --> 00:03:58,295
- I'm doing it.
- He's doing it.

131
00:03:58,695 --> 00:04:00,734
- It's fine.
- Do I have your respect now?

132
00:04:00,735 --> 00:04:02,205
- Okay.
- I got through.

133
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,774
Shall I park too?

134
00:04:03,775 --> 00:04:05,174
Yes, park. Over there.

135
00:04:05,175 --> 00:04:06,505
I'll show you. That would be fun.

136
00:04:06,645 --> 00:04:07,904
- Park over there.
- No.

137
00:04:07,905 --> 00:04:09,465
It's no fun if I park in a large space.

138
00:04:10,015 --> 00:04:11,174
Will we die tonight?

139
00:04:11,175 --> 00:04:12,314
You can't see behind the bus.

140
00:04:12,315 --> 00:04:14,014
- Go a bit to the left.
- Okay.

141
00:04:14,015 --> 00:04:15,315
Not that way. The other way.

142
00:04:15,515 --> 00:04:17,614
He did it. We can get out now.

143
00:04:17,615 --> 00:04:19,154
- You can park.
- That was pretty good.

144
00:04:19,155 --> 00:04:20,755
- I can park.
- You're pretty good.

145
00:04:20,985 --> 00:04:22,254
What do you think, boss?

146
00:04:22,255 --> 00:04:23,424
- That wasn't bad.
- That wasn't bad.

147
00:04:23,425 --> 00:04:24,454
It's 85 out of 100.

148
00:04:24,455 --> 00:04:25,495
- Thank you.
- Sure.

149
00:04:25,825 --> 00:04:27,365
Hey, Joon.

150
00:04:27,425 --> 00:04:28,425
- Joon.
- What?

151
00:04:28,426 --> 00:04:29,564
You're awesome at parking.

152
00:04:29,565 --> 00:04:30,665
Aren't I?

153
00:04:30,935 --> 00:04:32,065
- See?
- Well done.

154
00:04:32,805 --> 00:04:34,905
And now you can all get off.

155
00:04:35,205 --> 00:04:36,305
Well done.

156
00:04:36,635 --> 00:04:38,504
- He parked well.
- Not bad. You parked well.

157
00:04:38,505 --> 00:04:39,574
- Yes.
- You're good at driving.

158
00:04:39,575 --> 00:04:40,605
See?

159
00:04:40,875 --> 00:04:42,144
- Your skill...
- No.

160
00:04:42,145 --> 00:04:43,744
You can tell if someone's good or bad.

161
00:04:43,745 --> 00:04:44,944
- Good job.
- Not bad.

162
00:04:44,945 --> 00:04:47,014
Next time, Joon can drive us somewhere.

163
00:04:47,015 --> 00:04:48,015
Of course.

164
00:04:48,016 --> 00:04:49,176
- Most definitely.
- Not bad.

165
00:04:49,355 --> 00:04:50,555
You're good at this, Joon.

166
00:04:50,715 --> 00:04:52,924
- Parking's the hardest part.
- Joon's in charge.

167
00:04:52,925 --> 00:04:54,355
(They look forward to Joon's trip.)

168
00:04:54,655 --> 00:04:55,994
(Hot Spring, Spa, Sauna)

169
00:04:55,995 --> 00:04:58,224
It's cold. Gosh. It's cold.

170
00:04:58,225 --> 00:04:59,695
(Gosh. It's cold.)

171
00:05:00,025 --> 00:05:01,824
Gosh. It's cold.

172
00:05:01,825 --> 00:05:03,585
(He's the quickest when looking for warmth.)

173
00:05:03,665 --> 00:05:05,264
- This place...
- It's warm in here.

174
00:05:05,265 --> 00:05:07,105
(Where did they go to escape the cold?)

175
00:05:08,465 --> 00:05:11,204
(A hot spring to thaw their cold bodies)

176
00:05:11,205 --> 00:05:12,304
It's hot.

177
00:05:12,305 --> 00:05:14,045
- This is it.
- It's hot.

178
00:05:14,905 --> 00:05:16,144
It's the perfect temperature.

179
00:05:16,145 --> 00:05:17,345
It's 39.5°C.

180
00:05:17,775 --> 00:05:19,245
This is what we wanted.

181
00:05:19,345 --> 00:05:21,715
Let's do this sometimes, please. It's great.

182
00:05:22,085 --> 00:05:23,354
It's just the temperature I like.

183
00:05:23,355 --> 00:05:24,415
This is great.

184
00:05:24,815 --> 00:05:26,185
- Can we sit?
- Yes.

185
00:05:26,725 --> 00:05:27,754
This is lovely.

186
00:05:27,755 --> 00:05:29,855
This is what we want after a day in the cold.

187
00:05:29,995 --> 00:05:32,494
The hot water here comes from a spring that comes through...

188
00:05:32,495 --> 00:05:34,495
the rock bed of a famous mountain in Pohang.

189
00:05:34,795 --> 00:05:35,964
- My gosh, this is nice.
- Yes.

190
00:05:35,965 --> 00:05:37,865
- The water is from a hot spring?
- Yes.

191
00:05:38,495 --> 00:05:39,781
- Gosh, this is nice.
- Because...

192
00:05:39,805 --> 00:05:42,104
it's alkaline water, it's great for your skin,

193
00:05:42,105 --> 00:05:44,265
improves blood circulation, and helps relieve fatigue.

194
00:05:44,435 --> 00:05:46,075
- I have allergies. This is great.
- Yes.

195
00:05:46,445 --> 00:05:48,005
- Nice.
- For your dinner tonight,

196
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:51,474
we put together a meal with representative winter dishes from...

197
00:05:51,475 --> 00:05:53,384
- Pohang, the city of gastronomy.
- I had a feeling.

198
00:05:53,385 --> 00:05:54,484
I have to get dinner no matter what.

199
00:05:54,485 --> 00:05:56,014
- Did you get snow crab?
- Let me show you...

200
00:05:56,015 --> 00:05:57,884
- Snow crab.
- tonight's dinner.

201
00:05:57,885 --> 00:05:59,184
- You'll show us?
- I bet we're getting snow crab.

202
00:05:59,185 --> 00:06:00,985
- Show us.
- We'll see it on the screen?

203
00:06:01,925 --> 00:06:03,605
- My gosh.
- I told you. It was snow crab.

204
00:06:04,125 --> 00:06:05,254
- Gosh.
- Snow crab.

205
00:06:05,255 --> 00:06:06,664
We haven't had snow crab yet.

206
00:06:06,665 --> 00:06:08,995
What's that dish all the way on the top left corner?

207
00:06:09,795 --> 00:06:11,665
We prepared plump hard-shell snow crab...

208
00:06:12,195 --> 00:06:13,304
- Gosh, hard-shell snow crab.
- and...

209
00:06:13,305 --> 00:06:14,434
monkfish suyuk.

210
00:06:14,435 --> 00:06:15,974
- Monkfish suyuk?
- Monkfish. Oh, my.

211
00:06:15,975 --> 00:06:17,534
- There's also half-dried saury.
- It's half-dried saury.

212
00:06:17,535 --> 00:06:18,935
- It's half-dried saury.
- My gosh.

213
00:06:18,975 --> 00:06:20,144
We're getting one snow crab each.

214
00:06:20,145 --> 00:06:22,044
Right now, 1kg of snow crab goes up to 140 dollars.

215
00:06:22,045 --> 00:06:25,114
Your appetite will explode over this meal.

216
00:06:25,115 --> 00:06:27,184
A complete meal with Pohang delicacies...

217
00:06:27,185 --> 00:06:28,461
will be at stake on this mission.

218
00:06:28,485 --> 00:06:31,485
It's Sweaty Hot Bath and Karaoke.

219
00:06:31,715 --> 00:06:32,925
- My gosh.
- What?

220
00:06:33,325 --> 00:06:36,655
(Dancing)

221
00:06:36,995 --> 00:06:39,564
(Having fun, splashed)

222
00:06:39,565 --> 00:06:42,734
It's time for you to come together as a group...

223
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,495
- and play this mission.
- That's great.

224
00:06:44,565 --> 00:06:46,565
Joon, you're good at group missions.

225
00:06:46,765 --> 00:06:47,865
- Yes.
- Show us.

226
00:06:48,105 --> 00:06:49,105
Okay.

227
00:06:49,235 --> 00:06:51,275
You guys will get seven tries.

228
00:06:51,635 --> 00:06:52,875
- Seven tries?
- Yes.

229
00:06:53,005 --> 00:06:55,345
- It must be a hard one.
- Every time you fail,

230
00:06:55,545 --> 00:06:59,045
- you'll lose a dish one at a time.
- Come on.

231
00:06:59,315 --> 00:07:00,384
- That's the worst.
- See?

232
00:07:00,385 --> 00:07:01,784
That's why there were seven dishes.

233
00:07:01,785 --> 00:07:04,055
If you fail to succeed within seven tries,

234
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:06,284
you won't get any dinner.

235
00:07:06,285 --> 00:07:07,654
- What?
- What?

236
00:07:07,655 --> 00:07:08,755
No food at all?

237
00:07:08,785 --> 00:07:10,224
- Right.
- What?

238
00:07:10,225 --> 00:07:13,724
Every time you fail, you will lose a plate of snow crab first.

239
00:07:13,725 --> 00:07:14,994
- Why?
- My gosh.

240
00:07:14,995 --> 00:07:16,595
Then monkfish suyuk...

241
00:07:16,695 --> 00:07:18,835
and half-dried saury will be removed in order.

242
00:07:19,065 --> 00:07:20,905
- Okay.
- However,

243
00:07:21,465 --> 00:07:24,734
we will give you a chance card every time you fail.

244
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:25,905
- Okay.
- All right.

245
00:07:26,505 --> 00:07:28,275
The song you will sing...

246
00:07:28,705 --> 00:07:30,615
was in a KBS drama...

247
00:07:31,315 --> 00:07:33,844
that reached 53 percent viewership ratings...

248
00:07:33,845 --> 00:07:35,091
- What?
- when it aired in 1995.

249
00:07:35,115 --> 00:07:36,115
It was in a drama.

250
00:07:36,116 --> 00:07:38,631
- Is it "The Sunshine of the Youth??
- The late Lee Soon Jae...

251
00:07:38,655 --> 00:07:39,655
(The late Lee Soon Jae)

252
00:07:39,656 --> 00:07:42,025
Jang Yong, Go Doo Shim, Youn Yuh Jung,

253
00:07:42,655 --> 00:07:44,095
and Kim Hee Seon had the lead roles.

254
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:45,594
(A star-studded lineup, impossible to see these days)

255
00:07:45,595 --> 00:07:47,194
It's "Men of the Bath House."

256
00:07:47,195 --> 00:07:49,295
("Men of the Bath House")

257
00:07:49,565 --> 00:07:50,594
