this bad.

1036
00:33:33,178 --> 00:33:35,078
Jong Min, sing it like pansori.

1037
00:33:36,318 --> 00:33:38,488
- We'll go.
- This is your last try.

1038
00:33:38,788 --> 00:33:39,857
What was my part?

1039
00:33:39,858 --> 00:33:41,818
Play the song.

1040
00:33:41,918 --> 00:33:44,858
And lingering wishes

1041
00:33:45,958 --> 00:33:49,027
(Because the world we live in is trivial after all)

1042
00:33:49,028 --> 00:33:52,327
(He tells us to cherish and love one another)

1043
00:33:52,328 --> 00:33:54,467
(It's no one's fault)

1044
00:33:54,468 --> 00:33:56,037
(That some live well)

1045
00:33:56,038 --> 00:33:59,108
(While others don't)

1046
00:33:59,578 --> 00:34:01,977
(There are excuses for failing)

1047
00:34:01,978 --> 00:34:03,648
(And reasons to blame for losing)

1048
00:34:04,578 --> 00:34:06,678
(He finally escaped from "and reasons" inferno.)

1049
00:34:06,818 --> 00:34:08,448
(And...)

1050
00:34:08,878 --> 00:34:12,348
(Joon gets tested for the first time.)

1051
00:34:12,718 --> 00:34:15,088
(If Joon makes it, it'll be as good as a success.)

1052
00:34:15,388 --> 00:34:17,187
(They regret not following through)

1053
00:34:17,188 --> 00:34:18,958
(And make excuses for not even trying)

1054
00:34:19,258 --> 00:34:21,598
(The success is right around the corner.)

1055
00:34:22,528 --> 00:34:24,297
(Our home is full of fun)

1056
00:34:24,298 --> 00:34:25,767
(And happiness)

1057
00:34:25,768 --> 00:34:31,338
(You should come over, ha, ha, ha)

1058
00:34:31,738 --> 00:34:33,207
(Their seventh try is successful.)

1059
00:34:33,208 --> 00:34:34,608
All right!

1060
00:34:37,478 --> 00:34:41,547
(Without a doubt, DinDin is the ace of this game.)

1061
00:34:41,548 --> 00:34:42,618
Goodness.

1062
00:34:42,718 --> 00:34:44,888
He's our hero.

1063
00:34:45,418 --> 00:34:46,518
That's enough.

1064
00:34:47,558 --> 00:34:49,188
(Gurgling)

1065
00:34:49,788 --> 00:34:51,487
Here's the result.

1066
00:34:51,488 --> 00:34:53,498
As your last attempt was successful,

1067
00:34:54,398 --> 00:34:57,198
you've won half-dried saury.

1068
00:34:57,698 --> 00:35:00,538
(Although the start was lavish...)

1069
00:35:00,898 --> 00:35:03,167
We should eat some half-dried saury since it's in season.

1070
00:35:03,168 --> 00:35:04,607
Also, we're in Pohang.

1071
00:35:04,608 --> 00:35:06,207
Instead of eating snow crab today,

1072
00:35:06,208 --> 00:35:07,877
- we can eat crab sticks later.
- Right.

1073
00:35:07,878 --> 00:35:09,307
Congratulations, everyone.

1074
00:35:09,308 --> 00:35:10,807
Please go and have dinner.

1075
00:35:10,808 --> 00:35:12,248
- Yes!
- Yes.

1076
00:35:12,548 --> 00:35:13,548
(They escaped from the eternal bathhouse.)

1077
00:35:13,548 --> 00:35:14,548
Let's go.

1078
00:35:15,148 --> 00:35:16,847
A person who's hopeless has many excuses.

1079
00:35:16,848 --> 00:35:19,064
(Today's lesson: A person who's hopeless has many excuses.)

1080
00:35:19,088 --> 00:35:20,918
The air feels depressing.

1081
00:35:21,018 --> 00:35:23,287
We only have one dish of half-dried saury.

1082
00:35:23,288 --> 00:35:24,588
We got something at least.

1083
00:35:24,888 --> 00:35:26,027
Of course.

1084
00:35:26,028 --> 00:35:27,657
I'm sorry, but I'll sit here.

1085
00:35:27,658 --> 00:35:29,567
- Sure.
- I'm different from you guys.

1086
00:35:29,568 --> 00:35:31,798
- By the way...
- Right, he won the One-Bite Ticket.

1087
00:35:33,838 --> 00:35:36,908
(A war of One-Bite Ticket took place earlier during the day.)

1088
00:35:37,468 --> 00:35:41,938
(The result of running with his runner's pride on the line)

1089
00:35:42,408 --> 00:35:45,948
(DinDin won the One-Bite Ticket.)

1090
00:35:46,208 --> 00:35:47,947
DinDin won one bite.

1091
00:35:47,948 --> 00:35:48,977
(Relaxed)

1092
00:35:48,978 --> 00:35:50,847
I'm having a different meal from everyone else,

1093
00:35:50,848 --> 00:35:52,087
so I'll sit separately.

1094
00:35:52,088 --> 00:35:53,088
(Keeping a distance)

1095
00:35:53,089 --> 00:35:54,887
Today's game was...

1096
00:35:54,888 --> 00:35:56,687
the most difficult that we ever played.

1097
00:35:56,688 --> 00:35:58,687
- It wasn't easy.
- It was the most difficult.

1098
00:35:58,688 --> 00:36:01,828
I don't want our viewers to misunderstand that we're dumb.

1099
00:36:02,198 --> 00:36:03,198
That's what worries me.

1100
00:36:03,199 --> 00:36:05,597
It was hard. It's impossible to memorize a song we don't know.

1101
00:36:05,598 --> 00:36:06,637
- In case they misunderstand?
- It was hard.

1102
00:36:06,638 --> 00:36:08,097
I think DinDin misunderstood you.

1103
00:36:08,098 --> 00:36:11,007
- Did you?
- No, you guys aren't dumb.

1104
00:36:11,008 --> 00:36:12,407
(I didn't think that you were dumb.)

1105
00:36:12,408 --> 00:36:14,178
It's hard when I'm misunderstood.

1106
00:36:14,678 --> 00:36:16,908
- As a smart person?
- Yes, I get invited.

1107
00:36:17,278 --> 00:36:18,377
Who invited you?

1108
00:36:18,378 --> 00:36:22,577
What is that new show called on OTT?

1109
00:36:22,578 --> 00:36:23,717
They invited me to the show.

1110
00:36:23,718 --> 00:36:25,117
They said that I was good.

1111
00:36:25,118 --> 00:36:26,758
I responded arrogantly,

1112
00:36:27,258 --> 00:36:28,987
"Yes, I'm good on 2 Days 1 Night."

1113
00:36:28,988 --> 00:36:30,228
I decided to show up.

1114
00:36:30,328 --> 00:36:31,857
They asked me...

1115
00:36:31,858 --> 00:36:34,128
what games I was good at.

1116
00:36:34,428 --> 00:36:35,957
Here's what I'm good at.

1117
00:36:35,958 --> 00:36:38,968
Memorizing images on the back of the cards.

1118
00:36:39,068 --> 00:36:41,397
When I told them that,

1119
00:36:41,398 --> 00:36:44,367
they asked me for something else...

1120
00:36:44,368 --> 00:36:45,937
like chess, janggi, or number games.

1121
00:36:45,938 --> 00:36:48,177
I said, "I don't know about those, but I know capital cities."

1122
00:36:48,178 --> 00:36:49,514
(I'm good at guessing capital cities.)

1123
00:36:49,538 --> 00:36:50,547
(His brain is optimized for 2 Days 1 Night.)

1124
00:36:50,548 --> 00:36:52,147
They really overestimated you.

1125
00:36:52,148 --> 00:36:54,878
I saw Lee Se Dol and Jang Dong Min...

1126
00:36:54,948 --> 00:36:56,218
in the show's teaser.

1127
00:36:56,288 --> 00:36:58,018
Tell them with confidence.

1128
00:36:58,418 --> 00:37:00,317
On this show, you're Lee Se Dol.

1129
00:37:00,318 --> 00:37:01,587
Of course.

1130
00:37:01,588 --> 00:37:02,657
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

1131
00:37:02,658 --> 00:37:03,857
- Let's start.
- Thank you for the food.

1132
00:37:03,858 --> 00:37:04,888
Here's some oil.

1133
00:37:05,658 --> 00:37:07,657
I don't usually eat half-dried saury.

1134
00:37:07,658 --> 00:37:09,228
- I love it.
- This is very good.

1135
00:37:09,828 --> 00:37:11,127
This is crazy.

1136
00:37:11,128 --> 00:37:12,498
(Yes, this is the taste.)

1137
00:37:12,628 --> 00:37:14,174
I've also had it at a convenience store.

1138
00:37:14,198 --> 00:37:16,307
- At a convenience store?
- I love half-dried saury.

1139
00:37:16,308 --> 00:37:17,768
- It's really delicious.
- Gosh.

1140
00:37:18,008 --> 00:37:20,137
It tastes excellent in a good wrap.

1141
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:21,507
What's the best way to make a wrap?

1142
00:37:21,508 --> 00:37:22,637
They're all the same.

1143
00:37:22,638 --> 00:37:24,707
Put these on. It's very obvious.

1144
00:37:24,708 --> 00:37:26,108
Put these on.

1145
00:37:26,618 --> 00:37:28,348
Add some gochujang.

1146
00:37:28,918 --> 00:37:30,118
You have to add some garlic.

1147
00:37:30,448 --> 00:37:31,448
Garlic is a must.

1148
00:37:31,449 --> 00:37:33,358
(Eating it all in one bite is a must.)

1149
00:37:34,618 --> 00:37:36,117
(The savory flavor of half-dried saury spreads in the mouth.)

1150
00:37:36,118 --> 00:37:38,257
- Goodness.
- It's very rich in oil.

1151
00:37:38,258 --> 00:37:40,157
(The savory flavor of half-dried saury spreads in the mouth.)

1152
00:37:40,158 --> 00:37:42,098
I don't eat half-dried saury often.

1153
00:37:42,898 --> 00:37:44,467
Look, my mouth is watering.

1154
00:37:44,468 --> 00:37:45,997
(Jong Min enjoys it with seaweed and red algae.)

1155
00:37:45,998 --> 00:37:47,198
It's very big.

1156
00:37:51,638 --> 00:37:52,638
Oh, my.

1157
00:37:52,668 --> 00:37:53,808
It's very rich in oil.

1158
00:37:53,938 --> 00:37:54,977
Goodness.

1159
00:37:54,978 --> 00:37:56,447
(Crunchy and chewy)

1160
00:37:56,448 --> 00:37:58,008
- It's really good.
- Gosh.

1161
00:37:58,248 --> 00:37:59,277
(Softness of seaweed)

1162
00:37:59,278 --> 00:38:00,947
- It's really delicious.
- My mouth is watering.

1163
00:38:00,948 --> 00:38:03,318
(Crunchiness of red algae)

1164
00:38:03,718 --> 00:38:06,218
(Chewiness of half-dried saury)

1165
00:38:07,488 --> 00:38:10,787
(It's an orchestra of fantastic textures.)

1166
00:38:10,788 --> 00:38:12,387
Pohang half-dried saury is the best.

1167
00:38:12,388 --> 00:38:13,597
(Guryongpo half-dried saury is the best.)

1168
00:38:13,598 --> 00:38:16,227
Honestly, I like half-dried saury more than snow crabs.

1169
00:38:16,228 --> 00:38:17,897
- Really?
- Yes, I love it.

1170
00:38:17,898 --> 00:38:18,928
This is very delicious.

1171
00:38:19,368 --> 00:38:21,337
Gosh, stop exaggerating.

1172
00:38:21,338 --> 00:38:22,538
I'm being serious.

1173
00:38:23,168 --> 00:38:24,867
This is half-dried saury, yareu.

1174
00:38:24,868 --> 00:38:26,068
(I'll show you how to eat it.)

1175
00:38:26,138 --> 00:38:28,207
- "Yareu?" - I learned it from children.

1176
00:38:28,208 --> 00:38:29,208
I see.

1177
00:38:29,209 --> 00:38:30,507
Tonight's dinner eating show.

1178
00:38:30,508 --> 00:38:32,148
This is half-dried saury, yareu.

1179
00:38:32,278 --> 00:38:34,218
My son keeps saying "yareu."

1180
00:38:34,848 --> 00:38:36,317
- Right?
- Yes.

1181
00:38:36,318 --> 00:38:37,387
Exactly.

1182
00:38:37,388 --> 00:38:39,247
"Dad, what's for dinner tonight? We're having beef."

1183
00:38:39,248 --> 00:38:40,257
"Yareu."

1184
00:38:40,258 --> 00:38:41,287
They say that.

1185
00:38:41,288 --> 00:38:43,428
(It's also said to express excitement.)

1186
00:38:43,758 --> 00:38:45,227
We used to say that when we were kids.

1187
00:38:45,228 --> 00:38:46,288
What?

1188
00:38:46,358 --> 00:38:47,927
Didn't we say something like "cap?"

1189
00:38:47,928 --> 00:38:48,957
No.

1190
00:38:48,958 --> 00:38:50,628
We used to say "yareu" a lot.

1191
00:38:51,498 --> 00:38:53,267
- That's not true.
- We really said that.

1192
00:38:53,268 --> 00:38:54,468
- Really?
- Yes.

1193
00:38:54,868 --> 00:38:57,437
I guess it got popular again. That's fascinating.

1194
00:38:57,438 --> 00:38:58,438
(It's hard to verify, but let's say that he's right.)

1195
00:38:58,438 --> 00:38:59,438
It's really good.

1196
00:38:59,439 --> 00:39:02,577
DinDin's One-Bite Ticket for snow crab, yareu.

1197
00:39:02,578 --> 00:39:03,824
(Using his One-Bite Ticket for the snow crab)

1198
00:39:03,848 --> 00:39:05,077
- Snow crab?
- Yes.

1199
00:39:05,078 --> 00:39:07,948
We'll let you have a spoonful of it.

1200
00:39:08,918 --> 00:39:10,448
Gosh, look at that.

1201
00:39:10,718 --> 00:39:12,718
(From crab legs to crab fried rice)

1202
00:39:13,258 --> 00:39:14,357
It's huge.

1203
00:39:14,358 --> 00:39:16,257
- Yareu.
- Look at the legs.

1204
00:39:16,258 --> 00:39:18,257
You can get a lot of food with the One-Bite Ticket.

1205
00:39:18,258 --> 00:39:19,558
It's a big advantage.

1206
00:39:20,028 --> 00:39:21,997
He gets to put as much meat as he wants on the spoon?

1207
00:39:21,998 --> 00:39:23,328
- Yes.
- Goodness.

1208
00:39:24,568 --> 00:39:25,927
That's not one bite.

1209
00:39:25,928 --> 00:39:27,537
- Isn't that the entire crab?
- When you do this,

1210
00:39:27,538 --> 00:39:29,098
- Right.
- you can pull everything out.

1211
00:39:29,338 --> 00:39:30,567
(Plump meat)

1212
00:39:30,568 --> 00:39:31,868
- This...
- You're smart.

1213
00:39:32,008 --> 00:39:33,408
Should I put some rice on it?

1214
00:39:33,508 --> 00:39:35,508
Isn't it better to eat only the crab meat?

1215
00:39:36,208 --> 00:39:39,208
(Moist leg meat)

1216
00:39:39,648 --> 00:39:41,778
Meat from the claw, yareu.

1217
00:39:42,948 --> 00:39:44,247
(Gathering little by little)

1218
00:39:44,248 --> 00:39:46,118
That would be worth about 100 dollars.

1219
00:39:46,148 --> 00:39:47,458
I think this is the maximum.

1220
00:39:48,018 --> 00:39:49,517
- I can't add more.
- Right.

1221
00:39:49,518 --> 00:39:51,528
I can press it down, but I'm not sure.

1222
00:39:51,928 --> 00:39:53,198
That's a lot.

1223
00:39:53,258 --> 00:39:54,627
- Se Yoon.
- Gosh.

1224
00:39:54,628 --> 00:39:56,497
(Showing his one bite before eating)

1225
00:39:56,498 --> 00:39:58,927
- Is this it?
- You must eat as much as you can.

1226
00:39:58,928 --> 00:39:59,937
(Open your mouth as wide as possible)

1227
00:39:59,938 --> 00:40:01,968
One bite of snow crab, yareu.

1228
00:40:02,668 --> 00:40:05,108
That 1 bite is probably worth 100 dollars.

1229
00:40:05,508 --> 00:40:07,438
His mouth is too small. It's going to tear.

1230
00:40:08,008 --> 00:40:09,338
Push it in. Don't drop any.

1231
00:40:09,878 --> 00:40:11,798
- Give me what he drops.
- That's it. Well done.

1232
00:40:12,108 --> 00:40:13,377
He didn't drop any.

1233
00:40:13,378 --> 00:40:14,677
I want some of that fried rice.

1234
00:40:14,678 --> 00:40:15,818
(It looks so delicious.)

1235
00:40:17,418 --> 00:40:18,547
Look at him savoring it.

1236
00:40:18,548 --> 00:40:22,958
(DinDin is savoring the snow crab while chewing it well.)

1237
00:40:26,558 --> 00:40:28,328
What is it? It's Homigot.

1238
00:40:28,758 --> 00:40:29,758
(The freshness of Pohang sea)

1239
00:40:29,759 --> 00:40:30,928
The taste of Homigot.

1240
00:40:31,598 --> 00:40:32,898
Is it like eating at Homigot?

1241
00:40:33,098 --> 00:40:34,497
Caught fresh out of the sea?

1242
00:40:34,498 --> 00:40:37,538
(The freshness of Pohang sea is right in my mouth.)

1243
00:40:39,508 --> 00:40:40,508
Gosh.

1244
00:40:40,708 --> 00:40:43,137
(It must be delicious.)

1245
00:40:43,138 --> 00:40:44,477
- I shouldn't have pressed it...
- The crab?

1246
00:40:44,478 --> 00:40:46,307
- because it's soft and plump.
- That's how you eat it.

1247
00:40:46,308 --> 00:40:47,877
When I chew it,

1248
00:40:47,878 --> 00:40:49,848
the juice keeps coming out.

1249
00:40:50,218 --> 00:40:52,687
When will I get to eat this much snow crab...

1250
00:40:52,688 --> 00:40:53,957
in one bite?

1251
00:40:53,958 --> 00:40:55,158
- Right.
- You're right.

1252
00:40:55,958 --> 00:40:57,527
- It could be your last time...
- Yes.

1253
00:40:57,528 --> 00:40:58,588
Eating it like that.

1254
00:40:59,428 --> 00:41:00,498
I'm full.

1255
00:41:00,658 --> 00:41:01,798
We had quite a lot of food.

1256
00:41:02,498 --> 00:41:04,667
By the way,

1257
00:41:04,668 --> 00:41:06,168
this half-dried saury is amazing.

1258
00:41:06,538 --> 00:41:09,237
I rarely had amazing half-dried saury.

1259
00:41:09,238 --> 00:41:10,338
Maybe once in my life.

1260
00:41:11,038 --> 00:41:12,367
This is the best I ever had.

1261
00:41:12,368 --> 00:41:14,107
It tastes the best here.

1262
00:41:14,108 --> 00:41:15,707
- Thank you for the food.
- It was great.

1263
00:41:15,708 --> 00:41:17,228
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you.

1264
00:41:19,178 --> 00:41:22,118
(Soon, it's time to go to bed.)

1265
00:41:22,878 --> 00:41:27,358
(At 11:40pm, the temperature feels like minus 12°C.)

1266
00:41:28,018 --> 00:41:31,187
(We called the members to the 2nd floor of the lodging.)

1267
00:41:31,188 --> 00:41:32,558
- What?
- What is it?

1268
00:41:32,988 --> 00:41:34,058
Please come in.

1269
00:41:34,258 --> 00:41:35,897
- What's going on?
- What?

1270
00:41:35,898 --> 00:41:37,378
I guess two people are sleeping here.

1271
00:41:37,668 --> 00:41:38,997
- What?
- That's impossible. It's too short.

1272
00:41:38,998 --> 00:41:40,918
- Are we sleeping here?
- How can we sleep here?

1273
00:41:40,968 --> 00:41:41,968
What?

1274
00:41:42,268 --> 00:41:44,338
- Wait a minute.
- Is this for sleeping indoors?

1275
00:41:44,668 --> 00:41:46,737
- This is sleeping indoors?
- I think so.

1276
00:41:46,738 --> 00:41:48,177
But there are rooms with beds.

1277
00:41:48,178 --> 00:41:49,237
(There are so many rooms with beds.)

1278
00:41:49,238 --> 00:41:51,207
- They must be up to something.
- No.

1279
00:41:51,208 --> 00:41:54,148
- What's this?
- There are so many rooms here.

1280
00:41:54,648 --> 00:41:56,647
- What's going on?
- What could it be?

1281
00:41:56,648 --> 00:41:58,348
Everyone, let me explain.

1282
00:41:58,718 --> 00:42:00,157
- Okay.
- What is it?

1283
00:42:00,158 --> 00:42:02,518
Tonight, you'll be sleeping...

1284
00:42:03,018 --> 00:42:04,488
at three different places.

1285
00:42:05,488 --> 00:42:09,157
The first option is a bedroom with beds for each person.

1286
00:42:09,158 --> 00:42:10,227
My goodness.

1287
00:42:10,228 --> 00:42:11,997
- Beds for each person?
