2078
01:12:36,024 --> 01:12:37,853
- Hello.
- Hello.

2079
01:12:37,854 --> 01:12:39,330
(The owner is obviously waiting in the hot spring owner's car.)

2080
01:12:39,354 --> 01:12:42,494
(The lighting directors are waiting in the Lighting Car.)

2081
01:12:42,864 --> 01:12:45,763
(Meanwhile, in Team Production's car...)

2082
01:12:45,764 --> 01:12:46,863
(Production Car)

2083
01:12:46,864 --> 01:12:48,033
(The hiking gear is waiting.)

2084
01:12:48,034 --> 01:12:50,304
Don't be like this to me.

2085
01:12:51,134 --> 01:12:56,304
(Why are you being like this?)

2086
01:12:56,474 --> 01:12:58,043
What's the Heave-Ho Car?

2087
01:12:58,044 --> 01:12:59,690
(The members are curious about the last one left.)

2088
01:12:59,714 --> 01:13:01,343
- Heave-Ho Car?
- What's the Heave-Ho Car?

2089
01:13:01,344 --> 01:13:03,184
- It's go big or go home.
- This is a car?

2090
01:13:03,784 --> 01:13:06,254
For your information, the Heave-Ho Car...

2091
01:13:06,884 --> 01:13:07,884
is me.

2092
01:13:07,885 --> 01:13:09,824
(It's me.)

2093
01:13:10,024 --> 01:13:12,294
(It boasts a fuel efficiency of 10km per 1 Coke.)

2094
01:13:12,594 --> 01:13:15,354
(Heave-Ho Car, Director Joo Jong Hyun)

2095
01:13:15,454 --> 01:13:16,724
- What?
- The Heave-Ho Car.

2096
01:13:17,564 --> 01:13:18,564
Are you serious?

2097
01:13:19,164 --> 01:13:20,963
(The seat is ready.)

2098
01:13:20,964 --> 01:13:22,304
What is that?

2099
01:13:22,704 --> 01:13:24,633
He might collapse if I go.

2100
01:13:24,634 --> 01:13:25,794
I still must give you a ride.

2101
01:13:26,404 --> 01:13:28,410
- What could it be for Jong Hyun?
- What could it be?

2102
01:13:28,434 --> 01:13:31,343
I think it's a matter of avoiding the worst vehicle.

2103
01:13:31,344 --> 01:13:33,343
It's about a great view. It must be from the mountain.

2104
01:13:33,344 --> 01:13:34,374
Look at this.

2105
01:13:34,944 --> 01:13:36,583
What?

2106
01:13:36,584 --> 01:13:38,513
(Hiking gear of certainty)

2107
01:13:38,514 --> 01:13:39,854
They said we could open the car.

2108
01:13:39,984 --> 01:13:41,483
The hiking gear is left for us to see just like that?

2109
01:13:41,484 --> 01:13:43,653
Right. But they usually don't make any twists these days.

2110
01:13:43,654 --> 01:13:45,724
- No twists.
- That doesn't make sense at all.

2111
01:13:46,054 --> 01:13:47,353
They didn't make any twists for that?

2112
01:13:47,354 --> 01:13:49,194
They don't make any twists these days.

2113
01:13:49,464 --> 01:13:51,723
Gosh, one quick decision...

2114
01:13:51,724 --> 01:13:53,393
will affect us greatly.

2115
01:13:53,394 --> 01:13:54,833
Gosh, what is this?

2116
01:13:54,834 --> 01:13:56,703
(The vehicle types are all different.)

2117
01:13:56,704 --> 01:13:58,734
The owner sitting there...

2118
01:13:58,834 --> 01:14:00,173
is so out of the blue.

2119
01:14:00,174 --> 01:14:01,950
(The people in the vehicles are all different as well!)

2120
01:14:01,974 --> 01:14:03,144
I'm going to decide now.

2121
01:14:03,374 --> 01:14:04,543
- What is Se Yoon's decision?
- All right.

2122
01:14:04,544 --> 01:14:05,973
- I can decide now, right?
- You may all decide.

2123
01:14:05,974 --> 01:14:07,143
- It's time to decide.
- Right.

2124
01:14:07,144 --> 01:14:08,250
(Which ones will the members decide to ride?)

2125
01:14:08,274 --> 01:14:10,414
Se Yoon, DinDin, Jong Min, Seon Ho, Joon.

2126
01:14:10,914 --> 01:14:12,384
You may choose in that order.

2127
01:14:13,014 --> 01:14:15,783
How can I choose to ride another car after all these years?

2128
01:14:15,784 --> 01:14:17,184
- Right.
- The minibus driver said,

2129
01:14:17,784 --> 01:14:19,553
"I'm Jong Min's senior."

2130
01:14:19,554 --> 01:14:22,324
"I even sent Jong Min to the army."

2131
01:14:23,064 --> 01:14:25,424
(Even in rain or snow, he became the foot of the members.)

2132
01:14:25,934 --> 01:14:31,204
(The hidden contributor of the show, minibus driver)

2133
01:14:31,334 --> 01:14:32,403
(Would a guy like him send me to the mountain?)

2134
01:14:32,404 --> 01:14:34,674
How would he lie? He would never betray us.

2135
01:14:35,334 --> 01:14:36,543
I'm going with the driver.

2136
01:14:36,544 --> 01:14:37,974
(I'm going with the bus driver!)

2137
01:14:38,574 --> 01:14:41,444
(Se Yoon chooses the minibus.)

2138
01:14:41,744 --> 01:14:43,213
What do I do?

2139
01:14:43,214 --> 01:14:44,783
(It's DinDin's turn to choose.)

2140
01:14:44,784 --> 01:14:46,384
Gosh, this is so unpredictable.

2141
01:14:47,014 --> 01:14:48,714
The mountain is in there.

2142
01:14:49,224 --> 01:14:51,454
Does it make sense for the hiking gear to be in there?

2143
01:14:51,624 --> 01:14:52,654
It feels off, doesn't it?

2144
01:14:52,794 --> 01:14:55,523
- Couldn't there be a twist?
- But they don't make twists.

2145
01:14:55,524 --> 01:14:57,324
They just go with what is shown.

2146
01:14:57,724 --> 01:14:59,463
- "What?" - It's just put on you right away.

2147
01:14:59,464 --> 01:15:01,163
"It was inside the car." This is what they'll say.

2148
01:15:01,164 --> 01:15:02,964
Right. They never make any twists.

2149
01:15:03,264 --> 01:15:05,333
(He heads toward the Lighting Car this time.)

2150
01:15:05,334 --> 01:15:06,474
Can I believe you?

2151
01:15:06,774 --> 01:15:07,933
I don't believe in any religion.

2152
01:15:07,934 --> 01:15:10,204
We spent so many years together. Can I believe you?

2153
01:15:11,274 --> 01:15:12,274
Should I believe you?

2154
01:15:12,614 --> 01:15:14,213
Should I believe the lighting director or you?

2155
01:15:14,214 --> 01:15:15,534
(He's stuck between the two men.)

2156
01:15:16,114 --> 01:15:17,443
- Believe me.
- I'll never believe you.

2157
01:15:17,444 --> 01:15:18,984
You should believe in yourself.

2158
01:15:19,284 --> 01:15:20,714
(Torn)

2159
01:15:20,884 --> 01:15:21,983
I love you, sir.

2160
01:15:21,984 --> 01:15:25,554
(I love you, sir.)

2161
01:15:25,754 --> 01:15:27,923
(Did DinDin choose the Lighting Car in the end?)

2162
01:15:27,924 --> 01:15:28,994
Are you serious?

2163
01:15:29,764 --> 01:15:30,824
Are you serious?

2164
01:15:30,894 --> 01:15:32,733
- Why ask?
- I'm just asking.

2165
01:15:32,734 --> 01:15:34,893
- Why ask?
- You're with us? Okay.

2166
01:15:34,894 --> 01:15:36,604
I haven't closed the door yet. Why ask?

2167
01:15:36,934 --> 01:15:38,033
Why ask?

2168
01:15:38,034 --> 01:15:40,104
It's nothing. I'm just asking.

2169
01:15:40,204 --> 01:15:42,343
(He boldly chose to get on the Lighting Car.)

2170
01:15:42,344 --> 01:15:44,743
Are you serious? It's over once you put the belt on.

2171
01:15:44,744 --> 01:15:48,274
(It feels chilly inside for some reason.)

2172
01:15:49,844 --> 01:15:50,944
I won't choose this one.

2173
01:15:51,544 --> 01:15:53,684
I won't make any twists!

2174
01:15:53,784 --> 01:15:55,214
I'm just going to choose this one!

2175
01:15:55,924 --> 01:15:57,824
- I'm going with this one!
- Are you serious?

2176
01:15:58,054 --> 01:16:00,153
- Are you serious?
- I'm going to ride this one!

2177
01:16:00,154 --> 01:16:01,293
This one is too risky!

2178
01:16:01,294 --> 01:16:02,594
If there aren't any twists,

2179
01:16:02,664 --> 01:16:03,894
I'm going to twist everything!

2180
01:16:04,294 --> 01:16:05,394
It's too risky!

2181
01:16:05,894 --> 01:16:07,094
Hey, don't do it!

2182
01:16:07,394 --> 01:16:12,433
(DinDin chooses the Production Car.)

2183
01:16:12,434 --> 01:16:13,533
Who's next? Is it Seon Ho?

2184
01:16:13,534 --> 01:16:17,674
(What is the fate DinDin has chosen?)

2185
01:16:18,474 --> 01:16:20,343
- Heave-ho!
- Let's go!

2186
01:16:20,344 --> 01:16:22,644
(Jong Min chooses the Heave-Ho Car next.)

2187
01:16:22,684 --> 01:16:25,284
(Seon Ho chooses the Lighting Car.)

2188
01:16:25,544 --> 01:16:28,084
(Joon chooses the Hot Spring Owner Car.)

2189
01:16:28,114 --> 01:16:29,953
(Se Yoon: Minibus, DinDin: Production Car, )

2190
01:16:29,954 --> 01:16:31,723
(Jong Min: Heave-Ho Car, Seon Ho: Lighting Car, )

2191
01:16:31,724 --> 01:16:33,694
(Joon: Hot Spring Owner Car)

2192
01:16:33,924 --> 01:16:36,023
- That way!
- Let's go.

2193
01:16:36,024 --> 01:16:37,293
Bye!

2194
01:16:37,294 --> 01:16:39,834
(They each head to their own destination.)

2195
01:16:40,034 --> 01:16:43,764
(What will happen to them?)

2196
01:16:44,164 --> 01:16:46,003
Let's go! Heave-ho!

2197
01:16:46,004 --> 01:16:48,074
(The Heave-Ho Car leaves lastly with Jong Min.)

2198
01:16:48,204 --> 01:16:50,474
Let's go! Giddy-up!

2199
01:16:51,074 --> 01:16:52,973
Giddy-up! Keep going!

2200
01:16:52,974 --> 01:16:56,244
(Where will the Heave-Ho Car head to with Jong Min on the back?)

2201
01:16:57,444 --> 01:16:59,414
(Panting)

2202
01:16:59,614 --> 01:17:00,653
(Stopping)

2203
01:17:00,654 --> 01:17:02,154
This is a car as well.

2204
01:17:02,724 --> 01:17:03,883
What?

2205
01:17:03,884 --> 01:17:05,754
(Jong Min stops right at the entrance?)

2206
01:17:06,194 --> 01:17:07,854
- Let's head back.
- Where?

2207
01:17:08,494 --> 01:17:10,063
- Back there.
- Why?

2208
01:17:10,064 --> 01:17:11,763
We will wait for the other teams.

2209
01:17:11,764 --> 01:17:13,234
- What? Really?
- Yes.

2210
01:17:13,664 --> 01:17:15,804
- A few will come back.
- Really?

2211
01:17:16,304 --> 01:17:17,933
(Team Restaurant versus Team View)

2212
01:17:17,934 --> 01:17:19,574
(Where is this place?)

2213
01:17:19,874 --> 01:17:20,973
(Meanwhile, the other members are still moving.)

2214
01:17:20,974 --> 01:17:23,273
It feels scary as the car is heading out like this.

2215
01:17:23,274 --> 01:17:24,603
Do you know the destination?

2216
01:17:24,604 --> 01:17:25,643
I don't even know the destination.

2217
01:17:25,644 --> 01:17:26,644
- You don't?
- I don't.

2218
01:17:26,645 --> 01:17:28,173
- Really?
- I didn't get anything.

2219
01:17:28,174 --> 01:17:30,113
- They didn't tell you anything?
- Nothing.

2220
01:17:30,114 --> 01:17:32,383
When I watched the show at home,

2221
01:17:32,384 --> 01:17:34,583
I thought everything was planned ahead.

2222
01:17:34,584 --> 01:17:36,884
- Right.
- But...

2223
01:17:36,984 --> 01:17:39,393
- They don't tell you anything.
- they didn't tell me anything.

2224
01:17:39,394 --> 01:17:40,953
- Every single day here...
- Right.

2225
01:17:40,954 --> 01:17:42,293
Hurts my heart so much.

2226
01:17:42,294 --> 01:17:43,694
(It hurts my heart so much.)

2227
01:17:43,994 --> 01:17:45,663
Do I just get dragged there like this?

2228
01:17:45,664 --> 01:17:47,293
- What?
- Just like this?

2229
01:17:47,294 --> 01:17:48,493
We're heading there together.

2230
01:17:48,494 --> 01:17:50,803
- I chose this one because of you.
- Why is that?

2231
01:17:50,804 --> 01:17:53,233
You were the one I could trust the most.

2232
01:17:53,234 --> 01:17:54,474
Why are you giving me pressure?

2233
01:17:54,934 --> 01:17:57,844
If things go badly, it will affect our relationship a lot as well.

2234
01:17:58,244 --> 01:17:59,713
I decided to trust you.

2235
01:17:59,714 --> 01:18:01,090
(Will their friendship be able to be secure?)

2236
01:18:01,114 --> 01:18:04,884
(Meanwhile)

2237
01:18:05,144 --> 01:18:09,753
(The minibus feels like a noir film.)

2238
01:18:09,754 --> 01:18:11,883
(Minibus)

2239
01:18:11,884 --> 01:18:13,254
Where are we going?

2240
01:18:17,824 --> 01:18:20,164
(Quiet)

2241
01:18:21,864 --> 01:18:23,704
How long will we travel for, sir?

2242
01:18:25,034 --> 01:18:27,904
(No answer)

2243
01:18:28,704 --> 01:18:30,843
Is there supposed to be no response like this?

2244
01:18:30,844 --> 01:18:32,273
(Nodding)

2245
01:18:32,274 --> 01:18:34,020
(He's heading somewhere with an ominous silence.)

2246
01:18:34,044 --> 01:18:35,444
What did you have yesterday?

2247
01:18:35,744 --> 01:18:37,483
I had the half-dried saury yesterday.

2248
01:18:37,484 --> 01:18:38,813
- What about for lunch?
- A twisted donut.

2249
01:18:38,814 --> 01:18:40,113
- Just a twisted donut?
- Yes.

2250
01:18:40,114 --> 01:18:41,253
(Seon Ho started a talk show with the father-like director.)

2251
01:18:41,254 --> 01:18:43,753
It will be great to go hiking on a day like this.

2252
01:18:43,754 --> 01:18:45,430
- Is this the right day?
- The weather is great.

2253
01:18:45,454 --> 01:18:48,224
Your heart will be shattered if you see the mountain.

2254
01:18:48,354 --> 01:18:50,024
It will be shattered.

2255
01:18:50,294 --> 01:18:51,523
Shattered into pieces.

2256
01:18:51,524 --> 01:18:53,994
(They head to the destination without any time to get bored.)

2257
01:18:54,264 --> 01:18:56,764
(At that moment)

2258
01:18:56,904 --> 01:18:58,463
(Seon Ho's car)

2259
01:18:58,464 --> 01:18:59,604
Why are you being like this?

2260
01:19:00,474 --> 01:19:01,673
Why are you being like this?

2261
01:19:01,674 --> 01:19:03,273
(The Production Car is separating from the Lighting Car?)

2262
01:19:03,274 --> 01:19:04,373
What are you doing?

2263
01:19:04,374 --> 01:19:05,920
(The Production Car is separating from the Lighting Car?)

2264
01:19:05,944 --> 01:19:07,473
What? Why are they going that way?

2265
01:19:07,474 --> 01:19:10,184
(Why are we separating?)

2266
01:19:10,214 --> 01:19:11,983
(Production Car)

2267
01:19:11,984 --> 01:19:13,554
What are you doing?

2268
01:19:14,154 --> 01:19:15,923
What? Why?

2269
01:19:15,924 --> 01:19:17,424
(Startled)

2270
01:19:18,324 --> 01:19:22,424
(The cars are heading separate ways?)

2271
01:19:22,764 --> 01:19:24,863
What are you doing?

2272
01:19:24,864 --> 01:19:26,634
(Production Car)

2273
01:19:26,734 --> 01:19:27,893
Gosh, it's over.

2274
01:19:27,894 --> 01:19:29,203
(Lighting Car)

2275
01:19:29,204 --> 01:19:30,234
It's the mountain for me.

2276
01:19:30,904 --> 01:19:32,933
- Is that what you think?
- It's the mountain for me.

2277
01:19:32,934 --> 01:19:34,174
(An ominous feeling creeps up.)

2278
01:19:34,674 --> 01:19:38,404
(They move like that for a while.)

2279
01:19:38,674 --> 01:19:42,514
(Where are they all heading to?)

2280
01:19:42,784 --> 01:19:44,183
(He checks the GPS.)

2281
01:19:44,184 --> 01:19:46,253
What? We're here. This is our destination.

2282
01:19:46,254 --> 01:19:48,353
(Lighting Car)

2283
01:19:48,354 --> 01:19:50,153
We're in the downtown.

2284
01:19:50,154 --> 01:19:51,600
(Has the Lighting Car entered the downtown?)

2285
01:19:51,624 --> 01:19:53,594
(That means...)

2286
01:19:54,154 --> 01:19:56,294
(I did it!)

2287
01:19:58,724 --> 01:20:00,594
This isn't a place for a mountain view.

2288
01:20:01,464 --> 01:20:02,494
Hello?

2289
01:20:03,004 --> 01:20:04,064
Right.

2290
01:20:04,134 --> 01:20:06,903
- We put in the wrong address.
- He's acting.

2291
01:20:06,904 --> 01:20:08,834
- He's acting.
- Right.

2292
01:20:09,904 --> 01:20:12,174
Okay. We'll put it in again.

2293
01:20:12,204 --> 01:20:13,274
Okay.

2294
01:20:14,014 --> 01:20:16,943
Sir! Your phone didn't ring.

2295
01:20:16,944 --> 01:20:18,184
It did ring.

2296
01:20:18,744 --> 01:20:21,183
- My phone is quiet.
- Oh, come on!

2297
01:20:21,184 --> 01:20:22,630
(They arrive somewhere with his terrible acting.)

2298
01:20:22,654 --> 01:20:27,024
(It's a good restaurant.)

2299
01:20:27,224 --> 01:20:28,253
This must be it.

2300
01:20:28,254 --> 01:20:31,023
(I chose the right vehicle.)

2301
01:20:31,024 --> 01:20:32,594
I can head home after a nice meal.

2302
01:20:34,264 --> 01:20:36,203
(There's one person waiting in front of the restaurant.)

2303
01:20:36,204 --> 01:20:37,233
Awesome!

2304
01:20:37,234 --> 01:20:39,433
- Hey, brother!
- Hey, brother!

2305
01:20:39,434 --> 01:20:41,574
- Brother! Okay.
- Brother!

2306
01:20:42,434 --> 01:20:45,104
The foodies are back together.

2307
01:20:45,274 --> 01:20:47,744
- Gosh.
- He kept acting.

2308
01:20:48,614 --> 01:20:51,343
Se Yoon and Seon Ho, you two have arrived here.

2309
01:20:51,344 --> 01:20:53,214
Enjoy a filling meal here...

2310
01:20:53,454 --> 01:20:54,613
and head back home pleasantly.

2311
01:20:54,614 --> 01:20:55,614
(I love this.)

2312
01:20:55,615 --> 01:20:58,824
It's been a while for us to be together for food.

2313
01:20:59,054 --> 01:21:00,524
If the two of us are here,

2314
01:21:00,694 --> 01:21:02,323
are the other three hiking?

2315
01:21:02,324 --> 01:21:03,463
The other three are hiking.

2316
01:21:03,464 --> 01:21:04,524
No way.

2317
01:21:05,264 --> 01:21:06,904
"What?" He would've said this right away.

2318
01:21:06,994 --> 01:21:09,093
Within two minutes. "What?"

2319
01:21:09,094 --> 01:21:11,174
He would be saying, "There wasn't a twist for this?"

2320
01:21:12,334 --> 01:21:15,804
(You're right.)

2321
01:21:16,444 --> 01:21:17,444
What?

2322
01:21:17,445 --> 01:21:18,643
(He's with Jong Min.)

2323
01:21:18,644 --> 01:21:19,874
Why are you here?

2324
01:21:20,274 --> 01:21:22,743
(Joon's car comes into the parking lot...)

2325
01:21:22,744 --> 01:21:25,214
(where the two of them are waiting.)

2326
01:21:25,414 --> 01:21:30,424
(The three men have returned to the base camp.)

2327
01:21:30,924 --> 01:21:32,754
Three people were supposed to enjoy the view.

2328
01:21:32,954 --> 01:21:34,554
Why do you look so upset?

2329
01:21:35,454 --> 01:21:38,194
(If the three of us are here...)

2330
01:21:38,464 --> 01:21:39,494
Is it us?

2331
01:21:39,934 --> 01:21:41,734
Three people were supposed to enjoy the view.

2332
01:21:43,004 --> 01:21:44,034
Is it us?

2333
01:21:44,634 --> 01:21:47,604
From now on, we will move by foot.

2334
01:21:47,804 --> 01:21:49,073
- From here?
- Yes.

2335
01:21:49,074 --> 01:21:54,544
(They will enjoy the view.)

2336
01:21:54,774 --> 01:21:56,513
(The hint was as seen.)

2337
01:21:56,514 --> 01:21:58,243
Our destination...

2338
01:21:58,244 --> 01:22:00,483
is the place Gyeomjae Jeong Seon highly praised...

2339
01:22:00,484 --> 01:22:01,783
and drew a painting of.

2340
01:22:01,784 --> 01:22:03,100
(The mountain Gyeomjae Jeong Seon highly praised and drew of)

2341
01:22:03,124 --> 01:22:04,283
It's Mount Naeyeon.

2342
01:22:04,284 --> 01:22:05,624
- Mount Naeyeon?
- Yes.

2343
01:22:06,124 --> 01:22:09,254
(As for Mount Naeyeon, )

2344
01:22:09,524 --> 01:22:13,534
(it's a long course that takes over two hours for a full hike.)

2345
01:22:13,964 --> 01:22:18,064
(It even has an underworld of stairs.)

2346
01:22:18,204 --> 01:22:20,873
An amazing view was created by the gorges and cliffs.

2347
01:22:20,874 --> 01:22:22,404
Placed right at the top of that view,

2348
01:22:22,774 --> 01:22:24,874
we will be heading to...

2349
01:22:25,144 --> 01:22:26,414
Sogeumgang Observatory.

2350
01:22:26,814 --> 01:22:28,714
Let's go there to take in...

2351
01:22:28,874 --> 01:22:30,614
the beautiful view of the mountain.

2352
01:22:30,984 --> 01:22:32,753
(The train entrance is right next to the base camp.)

2353
01:22:32,754 --> 01:22:35,154
- Let's go.
- Okay.

2354
01:22:35,814 --> 01:22:36,984
All right.

2355
01:22:37,884 --> 01:22:38,884
This is the beginning.

2356
01:22:39,654 --> 01:22:41,574
- The scenery is beautiful already.
- Seriously,

2357
01:22:41,894 --> 01:22:43,824
why do I hate hiking so much?

2358
01:22:44,294 --> 01:22:45,793
Everyone has their own memories.

2359
01:22:45,794 --> 01:22:46,863
I have a trauma.

2360
01:22:46,864 --> 01:22:48,063
- There are things you hate.
- Everyone has it.

2361
01:22:48,064 --> 01:22:50,364
I woke up at 8am this morning...

2362
01:22:50,734 --> 01:22:52,974
as if I was possessed by a ghost.

2363
01:22:53,274 --> 01:22:55,404
I woke up right away and ran down the stairs.

2364
01:22:55,734 --> 01:22:57,474
- Did you arrive in second place?
- Yes.

2365
01:22:57,604 --> 01:22:58,944
- Really?
- I barely slept.

2366
01:22:59,414 --> 01:23:02,474
(Right before the wake-up song)

2367
01:23:03,484 --> 01:23:06,884
(Automatic reaction)

2368
01:23:07,354 --> 01:23:09,884
(He stayed up and waited for the wake-up song.)

2369
01:23:09,954 --> 01:23:13,953
I don't even want to set foot in this scenery.

2370
01:23:13,954 --> 01:23:15,294
- I know how you feel.
- Right.

2371
01:23:16,564 --> 01:23:17,763
I know the feeling.

2372
01:23:17,764 --> 01:23:18,823
(I know the feeling.)

2373
01:23:18,824 --> 01:23:20,634
- I understand.
- I do understand.

2374
01:23:20,894 --> 01:23:21,894
Right.

2375
01:23:21,895 --> 01:23:23,364
This is so frozen.

2376
01:23:24,534 --> 01:23:25,534
What?

2377
01:23:25,535 --> 01:23:26,974
What is it called?

2378
01:23:27,134 --> 01:23:28,174
The stream.

2379
01:23:29,134 --> 01:23:30,414
You couldn't think of that word?

2380
01:23:30,444 --> 01:23:31,973
(His head is frozen in the cold weather.)

2381
01:23:31,974 --> 01:23:33,014
Unbelievable.

2382
01:23:34,244 --> 01:23:35,643
Let's break the ice before we go.

2383
01:23:35,644 --> 01:23:37,144
Let's go in there, Joon.

2384
01:23:37,414 --> 01:23:40,553
If you get in the water, you don't have to go hiking.

2385
01:23:40,554 --> 01:23:41,584
What do you say, DinDin?

2386
01:23:42,154 --> 01:23:43,323
Then, I'll go in.

2387
01:23:43,324 --> 01:23:44,484
- Seriously?
- Are you sure?

2388
01:23:44,684 --> 01:23:45,824
You hate it that much?

2389
01:23:46,194 --> 01:23:48,723
This is like the process of patience.

2390
01:23:48,724 --> 01:23:50,624
The whole way up, I'm like...

2391
01:23:51,294 --> 01:23:52,294
It's boring.

2392
01:23:52,724 --> 01:23:54,864
It's hard that I'm out of breath.

2393
01:23:56,094 --> 01:23:57,263
(While he's hiking, which he hates more than getting into the water)

2394
01:23:57,264 --> 01:23:59,333
The stream is beautiful.

2395
01:23:59,334 --> 01:24:01,434
- The rocks are so cool.
- They really are.

2396
01:24:01,604 --> 01:24:02,704
- The rocks.
- Yes.

2397
01:24:04,144 --> 01:24:05,173
(Meanwhile, Team Restaurant)

2398
01:24:05,174 --> 01:24:06,343
My mouth is watering.

2399
01:24:06,344 --> 01:24:07,614
Can we eat this now?

2400
01:24:08,214 --> 01:24:10,084
(Pohang's local dish and 1 of the 10 best)

2401
01:24:10,684 --> 01:24:12,213
- It has monkfish in it.
- It's monkfish.

2402
01:24:12,214 --> 01:24:13,860
(The soup is rich and spicy with seasonal seafood and bean sprouts.)

2403
01:24:13,884 --> 01:24:16,724
(Mori guksu full of various nutrients)

2404
01:24:16,754 --> 01:24:18,523
Please tell us what mori guksu is.

2405
01:24:18,524 --> 01:24:20,823
It's a noodle dish made from seafood...

2406
01:24:20,824 --> 01:24:22,994
- that has no commercial value.
- They collect them?

2407
01:24:23,194 --> 01:24:24,863
- Assorted seafood.
- That's why?

2408
01:24:24,864 --> 01:24:27,764
And they make it spicy.

2409
01:24:27,994 --> 01:24:29,963
That's why it's called mori guksu.

2410
01:24:29,964 --> 01:24:31,563
Mori means assorted seafood.

2411
01:24:31,564 --> 01:24:32,804
That would be the best.

2412
01:24:32,904 --> 01:24:34,973
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you, Director.

2413
01:24:34,974 --> 01:24:36,943
- My pleasure.
- No, he's not a director. Sir.

2414
01:24:36,944 --> 01:24:38,180
(Experiencing the aftereffects of talking to Gi Jong)

2415
01:24:38,204 --> 01:24:40,244
- We finally get to eat this.
- I know.

2416
01:24:40,914 --> 01:24:41,974
I'll try the soup first.

2417
01:24:42,544 --> 01:24:43,683
I'll try the soup too.

2418
01:24:43,684 --> 01:24:45,564
(A real gourmet knows the taste from the soup.)

2419
01:24:47,654 --> 01:24:49,954
- Oh, dear.
- My gosh. This is wrong.

2420
01:24:51,184 --> 01:24:52,383
This is very wrong.

2421
01:24:52,384 --> 01:24:53,924
(This isn't just a noodle dish.)

2422
01:24:54,254 --> 01:24:57,424
It has monkfish and cod in it.

2423
01:24:57,724 --> 01:24:59,963
- And blue crabs.
- There are also fish innards.

2424
01:24:59,964 --> 01:25:00,993
There are also clams.

2425
01:25:00,994 --> 01:25:03,463
It tastes like the most refreshing seafood soup...

2426
01:25:03,464 --> 01:25:04,903
- with noodles.
- Exactly.

2427
01:25:04,904 --> 01:25:05,904
That's how it feels.

2428
01:25:06,134 --> 01:25:07,634
(Blowing)

2429
01:25:07,834 --> 01:25:10,234
I had to eat quickly yesterday, but I'll take my time today.

2430
01:25:10,304 --> 01:25:11,444
(Laughing)

2431
01:25:12,704 --> 01:25:14,043
Chew thoroughly, son.

2432
01:25:14,044 --> 01:25:15,644
(He can say that with confidence today.)

2433
01:25:16,414 --> 01:25:18,414
(Taking a big bite)

2434
01:25:19,114 --> 01:25:21,454
(The slurping refreshes those who are watching it.)

2435
01:25:21,554 --> 01:25:22,713
The noodles are...

2436
01:25:22,714 --> 01:25:23,883
(The noodles are cooked just right.)

2437
01:25:23,884 --> 01:25:24,924
They're perfect.

2438
01:25:25,554 --> 01:25:27,294
I finished the entire bowl in two bites.

2439
01:25:29,524 --> 01:25:32,023
(The portion is generous, so he's devouring it without holding back.)

2440
01:25:32,024 --> 01:25:34,693
This is insane.

2441
01:25:34,694 --> 01:25:35,694
You know what?

2442
01:25:36,364 --> 01:25:37,564
You should be quick-witted.

2443
01:25:38,304 --> 01:25:39,603
I opened the bus door and looked.

2444
01:25:39,604 --> 01:25:40,673
(They seemed a little scary.)

2445
01:25:40,674 --> 01:25:41,733
I was a little scared,

2446
01:25:41,734 --> 01:25:43,743
- but numbers 1 to 3 were there.
- Exactly.

2447
01:25:43,744 --> 01:25:45,544
The top four of Team Preparations were there.

2448
01:25:45,644 --> 01:25:47,173
And the top three of Team Security were there.

2449
01:25:47,174 --> 01:25:48,414
- Right.
- Top three.

2450
01:25:48,574 --> 01:25:49,783
Were there that many people?

2451
01:25:49,784 --> 01:25:52,213
Yes, they were there. I thought they were going to kill someone.

2452
01:25:52,214 --> 01:25:53,214
Really?

2453
01:25:53,654 --> 01:25:55,054
They were all dressed in black.

2454
01:25:55,454 --> 01:25:56,623
"What do I do?"

2455
01:25:56,624 --> 01:25:58,583
I looked ahead thinking that.

2456
01:25:58,584 --> 01:26:00,584
And I saw the youngest one of Team Preparations...

2457
01:26:01,094 --> 01:26:02,723
- playing games.
- Playing games?

2458
01:26:02,724 --> 01:26:03,893
He was playing games.

2459
01:26:03,894 --> 01:26:05,614
(Playing a game in that situation means...)

2460
01:26:05,894 --> 01:26:08,464
(Glancing)

2461
01:26:08,894 --> 01:26:11,004
(I think I managed to avoid the mountain.)

2462
01:26:11,104 --> 01:26:14,334
(Flustered)

2463
01:26:14,534 --> 01:26:16,873
"You don't seem to be in a bad mood."

2464
01:26:16,874 --> 01:26:18,074
(Excited)

2465
01:26:18,504 --> 01:26:20,274
(That's amazing.)

2466
01:26:20,674 --> 01:26:24,284
(His hands were shaking like this.)

2467
01:26:24,514 --> 01:26:25,683
- That's when you realized?
- Of course.

2468
01:26:25,684 --> 01:26:27,183
I was certain.

2469
01:26:27,184 --> 01:26:29,513
"This bus is going to a restaurant."

2470
01:26:29,514 --> 01:26:31,284
You made a good choice.

2471
01:26:31,584 --> 01:26:33,424
I was practically being fooled.

2472
01:26:34,394 --> 01:26:36,394
"Seon Ho, do you think you made the right choice?"

2473
01:26:38,524 --> 01:26:40,094
"Don't you regret your choice?"

2474
01:26:41,434 --> 01:26:43,063
"Yes. Unplug the cord first."

2475
01:26:43,064 --> 01:26:45,080
(Seon Ho swallowed Gi Jong during the past 30 minutes.)

2476
01:26:45,104 --> 01:26:46,774
Does Gi Jong get a script?

2477
01:26:47,974 --> 01:26:49,334
How could he say such a thing?

2478
01:26:49,434 --> 01:26:51,104
He was like that for 30 minutes.

2479
01:26:51,304 --> 01:26:52,844
- What?
- For 30 minutes.

2480
01:26:53,214 --> 01:26:54,314
But I guess...

2481
01:26:54,674 --> 01:26:56,614
he didn't ask you about the recent news.

2482
01:26:59,144 --> 01:27:00,214
Thank you, Director.

2483
01:27:01,884 --> 01:27:03,023
What do young people these days do?

2484
01:27:03,024 --> 01:27:04,554
(But the second oldest member asks.)

2485
01:27:05,624 --> 01:27:07,354
I'm having indigestion suddenly.

2486
01:27:08,324 --> 01:27:09,493
So, what do you do?

2487
01:27:09,494 --> 01:27:10,563
(He's curious about the youngest's life.)

2488
01:27:10,564 --> 01:27:11,604
What do you do these days?

2489
01:27:11,694 --> 01:27:14,333
I just can't eat. Seriously.

2490
01:27:14,334 --> 01:27:15,964
(Do you want me to eat or not?)

2491
01:27:16,034 --> 01:27:17,663
I've never seen Seon Ho leave food like that.

2492
01:27:17,664 --> 01:27:18,834
I can't eat.

2493
01:27:19,334 --> 01:27:21,103
What did you do on your dates?

2494
01:27:21,104 --> 01:27:22,624
I just waited at the baseball stadium.

2495
01:27:23,544 --> 01:27:24,544
Until she finished work.

2496
01:27:24,545 --> 01:27:25,673
(Suddenly curious about the second oldest's dating story)

2497
01:27:25,674 --> 01:27:27,194
I just waited at the baseball stadium.

2498
01:27:27,774 --> 01:27:28,843
Until she finished work.

2499
01:27:28,844 --> 01:27:31,014
So I was most annoyed when the game ended in a draw.

2500
01:27:31,114 --> 01:27:32,983
- Because it takes a long time?
- "Let anyone win!"

2501
01:27:32,984 --> 01:27:34,984
(He hates overtime. The winning team is his team.)

2502
01:27:35,014 --> 01:27:36,974
Back then, I watched the games in the car on DMB.

2503
01:27:37,424 --> 01:27:38,553
"Please."

2504
01:27:38,554 --> 01:27:39,793
- With the antenna?
- Yes.

2505
01:27:39,794 --> 01:27:41,393
"Arrived at second base! Runner on second base!"

2506
01:27:41,394 --> 01:27:42,593
"To come from behind!"

2507
01:27:42,594 --> 01:27:44,123
"The walk-off hit!"

2508
01:27:44,124 --> 01:27:46,493
"He's out at home plate!"

2509
01:27:46,494 --> 01:27:48,663
"The game will go into extra innings."

2510
01:27:48,664 --> 01:27:49,733
"Darn it!"

2511
01:27:49,734 --> 01:27:51,264
(A bolt from the blue)

2512
01:27:52,164 --> 01:27:54,004
"This is so frustrating."

2513
01:27:54,834 --> 01:27:56,234
I opened the door and went out.

2514
01:27:56,804 --> 01:27:58,303
(Not suitable for broadcast)

2515
01:27:58,304 --> 01:27:59,874
I was like this. "Darn it!"

2516
01:28:01,374 --> 01:28:02,974
This is what baseball fans do.

2517
01:28:03,714 --> 01:28:06,454
I didn't care who won. I just wanted to see my wife.

2518
01:28:06,654 --> 01:28:08,254
That's what I did.

2519
01:28:08,384 --> 01:28:09,384
That's romantic.

2520
01:28:09,385 --> 01:28:11,984
I loved the Twins, but I hated them when it happened.

2521
01:28:12,324 --> 01:28:13,494
What's this?

2522
01:28:13,994 --> 01:28:15,093
This is amazing.

2523
01:28:15,094 --> 01:28:16,393
(Meanwhile, the 3 hikers)

2524
01:28:16,394 --> 01:28:17,694
This is huge.

2525
01:28:19,194 --> 01:28:22,094
(Unfolding along the stream)

2526
01:28:22,994 --> 01:28:26,334
(The breathtaking scenery of Mount Naeyeon)

2527
01:28:26,774 --> 01:28:29,743
Mount Naeyeon has 12 waterfalls,

2528
01:28:29,744 --> 01:28:31,573
and this is one of them. It's called Sangsaeng Falls.

2529
01:28:31,574 --> 01:28:32,574
Sangsaeng Falls?

2530
01:28:32,575 --> 01:28:34,273
It's called Sangsaeng Falls,

2531
01:28:34,274 --> 01:28:35,913
meaning "living together," as it has two streams.

2532
01:28:35,914 --> 01:28:37,584
- I see.
- The two streams live together.

2533
01:28:37,744 --> 01:28:39,013
They live together.

2534
01:28:39,014 --> 01:28:45,154
(It is even more magnificent dressed in the beauty of winter.)

2535
01:28:46,154 --> 01:28:47,323
This is frozen solid.

2536
01:28:47,324 --> 01:28:50,623
It's frozen solid. The ice is incredibly thick.

2537
01:28:50,624 --> 01:28:52,763
It's really thick.

2538
01:28:52,764 --> 01:28:54,524
- Is this frozen?
- I can see the thickness.

2539
01:28:54,834 --> 01:28:56,714
- It's frozen. Look. It's thick.
- It's frozen.

2540
01:28:57,004 --> 01:28:58,933
This is frozen solid. I can feel it.

2541
01:28:58,934 --> 01:29:00,474
It's really hard.

2542
01:29:00,734 --> 01:29:02,273
The ice here is solid.

2543
01:29:02,274 --> 01:29:03,303
(It is filmed safely with the help of the safety personnel.)

2544
01:29:03,304 --> 01:29:05,873
- I can tell the ice is solid.
- It's really hard.

2545
01:29:05,874 --> 01:29:07,313
This is amazing.

2546
01:29:07,314 --> 01:29:08,713
You can skate here.

2547
01:29:08,714 --> 01:29:09,984
Let's ski.

2548
